Editors: Morris Eaves, University of Rochester;
Robert Essick, University of California, Riverside; and
Joseph Viscomi, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill

provenance.note:
Acquired from Blake by Charles Heathcote Tatham in Oct. 1799 (according to an inscription, perhaps by Tatham, on the verso of Object 1, reading "From the author / to C H Tatham Oct
          r
          ). 7 / 1799"); apparently Mary Taylor, who inscribed "Mary Taylor London" and a small drawing of a branch or vine on the verso of Object 1; possibly the copy sold from the collection of Edward Vernon Utterson, Sotheby's, 5 July 1852, lot 251 (£2.7s. to [James?] Holmes); perhaps the copy sold at a Puttick & Simpson auction, London, 25 May 1854, lot 95 (£5); sold in 1874 for £18 (according to Sotheby's 1878 catalogue); Albert George Dew-Smith; sold from Dew-Smith's collection, Sotheby's, 29 Jan. 1878, lot 247 (£16.5s. to the dealer John Pearson); Thomas Gaisford; sold from Gaisford's collection, Sotheby's, 23 April 1890, lot 189 (£61 to the dealer Bernard Quaritch); offered by Quaritch in his "Rough List" 104 of May 1890, item 460 (£68); acquired by Bernard Buchanan Macgeorge no later than 1892; sold from Macgeorge's collection, Sotheby's, 1 July 1924, lot 114 (£215 to the dealer Maggs Bros.); acquired by George C. Smith no later than 1927; sold from Smith's collection, Parke-Bernet, 2 Nov. 1938, lot 22 ($2600 to the dealer Rosenbach and Co., probably acting for Mrs. Landon K. Thorne); given by Thorne to the Pierpont Morgan Library (now Morgan Library and Museum) in 1973.
